This paper is about Semantic Role Labeling (SRL), which is a subfield of Natural Language Processing (NLP). The paper proposes a novel approach for SRL using a sequence-to-sequence model with attention and a copying mechanism. Therefore, the most likely category is cs.CL (Computation and Language), which is the main category for NLP research. The paper also uses machine learning techniques, such as deep learning and neural networks, which are covered in categories such as cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper mentions the need for further structural decoding constraints, which could be related to optimization and algorithms, covered in categories such as cs.NE (Neural and Evolutionary Computing). Finally, the paper uses PropBank SRL on English language data, which involves analyzing and processing text and could be related to computer vision, covered in category cs.CV (Computer Vision and Pattern Recognition).
